snippet.textDisplay: I'm young but in the chronic condition category, pregnant and constantly exposed to covid. Just this week 10 of my students tested positive. My doctor recommended I get a booster. The 4th didn't make my arm sore or give me any fever like the last one did. I was surpised.  My 3rd shot was way back in October. And before you all freak out, my high risk maternal medicine specialist approved me. She's awesome and baby is vibing in the juices as usual.
